{"id":2686,"date":"2022-09-16T10:13:12","date_gmt":"2022-09-16T10:13:12","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/garekarsmdskinclinic.com\/?page_id=2686"},"modified":"2022-11-21T10:55:19","modified_gmt":"2022-11-21T10:55:19","slug":"chemical-peeling","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/garekarsmdskinclinic.com\/chemical-peeling\/","title":{"rendered":"Chemical peeling"},"content":{"rendered":"<!-- About -->\r\n<section class=\"about section-padding\">\r\n    <div class=\"container\">\r\n    <div class=\"row\">\r\n    <div class=\"col-md-6 mb-30 animate-box\" data-animate-effect=\"fadeInUp\">\r\n    <!--<div class=\"section-subtitle\">Garekars MD<\/div>-->\r\n    <div class=\"section-title\"><h2> What is chemical peeling? <\/h2><\/div>\r\n<p>    Chemical peels are carried out by dermatologist as an in-clinic procedure to manage various skin concerns. The procedure involves application of specific chemical agents in pre-determined concentrations on to the skin.<\/p>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    <!-- reservation -->\r\n    <div class=\"reservations\">\r\n        <div class=\"butn-dark\"><a href=\"https:\/\/garekarsmdskinclinic.com\/get-appointment\/\"><span> Get appointment<\/span><\/a><\/div>\r\n        <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\r\n    <div class=\"text\">\r\n    Call us\r\n    <a href=\"tel:9667684409\">96501 44438<\/a>\r\n    <\/div>\r\n    <\/div>\r\n    <\/div>\r\n    <div class=\"col col-md-6 animate-box\" data-animate-effect=\"fadeInUp\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/garekarsmdskinclinic.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/09\/chemical-peels-treatment-in-gurgaon.jpg\" alt=\"Chemical Peels in Treatment Gurgaon\" \/><\/div>\r\n    <!--\r\n    <div class=\"col col-md-3 animate-box\" data-animate-effect=\"fadeInUp\"> <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"img\/900x1200.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/div>\r\n    -->\r\n    \r\n    <\/div>\r\n    <\/div>\r\n    <\/section><!-- Faqs -->\r\n    \r\n    <section class=\"section-padding bg-cream\">\r\n    <div class=\"container\">\r\n        <div class=\"row\">\r\n    \r\n            <div class=\"col-md-12\">\r\n                <div class=\"section-subtitle\">F.A.Qs<\/div>\r\n                <div class=\"section-title\">            <h2>About Chemical peeling                <\/h2>            <\/div>\r\n            <ul class=\"accordion-box clearfix\">\r\n                    <li class=\"accordion block\">\r\n                    <div class=\"acc-btn\"> How is it done?<\/div>\r\n                    <div class=\"acc-content\" style=\"display: none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"content\">\r\n                    <div class=\"text\">At Garekars MD, the peeling session is about 30-40 minutes duration. The steps involve initially scrubbing, exfoliation, hydration and comedone extraction. This is followed by the application of the peel by the dermatologist.\r\n                    <\/div>\r\n                    <\/div>\r\n                    <\/div>\r\n                    <\/li>\r\n    \r\n                    <li class=\"accordion block\">\r\n                    <div class=\"acc-btn\"> Is it safe?<\/div>\r\n                    <div class=\"acc-content\">\r\n                    <div class=\"content\">\r\n                    <div class=\"text\">\r\n                        Chemical peels are absolutely safe provided they are done under the supervision of a dermatologist.\r\n                        <\/div>\r\n                    <\/div>\r\n                    <\/div>\r\n                    <\/li>\r\n                    \r\n                    <li class=\"accordion block\">\r\n                        <div class=\"acc-btn\">What are the benefits of Chemical peeling?<\/div>\r\n                        <div class=\"acc-content\">\r\n                        <div class=\"content\">\r\n                        <div class=\"text\">\r\n                        Chemical peels can be used to address various skin concerns:\r\n                        <ol>\r\n                        <li>Acne <\/li>\r\n                        <li>Pigmentation<\/li>\r\n                        <li>Fine lines<\/li>\r\n                        <li>Dullness <\/li>\r\n                        <li>Photoaging <\/li>\r\n    \r\n                        <\/ol>    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n                        <\/div>\r\n                        <\/div>\r\n                    <\/li>\r\n                                    \r\n                    <li class=\"accordion block\">\r\n                        <div class=\"acc-btn\">What are the benefits of Chemical peeling?<\/div>\r\n                        <div class=\"acc-content\">\r\n                        <div class=\"content\">\r\n                        <div class=\"text\">\r\n                            There are different peels for managing different concerns.\r\n                        <ol>\r\n                        <li>Salicylic peel <\/li>\r\n                        <li>Yellow peel<\/li>\r\n                        <li>Glycolic peel<\/li>\r\n                        <li>TCA peel <\/li>\r\n                        <li>Black peel <\/li>\r\n    \r\n                        <\/ol>    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n                        <\/div>\r\n                        <\/div>\r\n                    <\/li>\r\n                        \r\n                    <li class=\"accordion block\">\r\n                        <div class=\"acc-btn\">What are the post-procedure precautions?<\/div>\r\n                        <div class=\"acc-content\">\r\n                        <div class=\"content\">\r\n                        <div class=\"text\">\r\n                            There are different peels for managing different concerns.\r\n                        <ol>\r\n                        <li>You might experience mild itching or redness on treated area for next 24-48 hours. <\/li>\r\n                        <li>Use only cleanser, moisturiser and sunscreen on treated area for 03 days post procedure. <\/li>\r\n                        <li>Don\u2019t use any scrubs, loofahs, facial steamers, anti acne creams, serums, anti- aging creams or any other ointments prescribed to you other than moisturiser and sunscreen for 03 days post procedure. <\/li>\r\n                        <li>Do not tweeze, rub, pick, bleach, wax or exfoliate the treated area for 01 week post Procedure. <\/li>\r\n                        <li>Do not take any other treatments like laser, peeling, medifacial\/medispa, for 01 week post procedure. <\/li>\r\n                        <li>Use moisturiser and sunscreen every 4-5 hourly and avoid activities involving prolonged direct sun exposure like swimming, hiking for 03 days post procedure.<\/li>\r\n                        <\/ol>    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n                        <\/div>\r\n                        <\/div>\r\n                    <\/li>\r\n                    <\/ul>\r\n                <\/div>\r\n          \r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"col-md-12\">\r\n    <div class=\"reservations\">\r\n        <div class=\"butn-dark\"><a href=\"https:\/\/garekarsmdskinclinic.com\/get-appointment\/\"><span> Get appointment<\/span><\/a><\/div>\r\n        <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\r\n    <div class=\"text\">Call us\r\n    <a href=\"tel:96501 44438\">9667684409<\/a><\/div>\r\n    <\/div>\r\n    <\/div>\r\n    <\/div>\r\n    <\/div>\r\n    <\/section>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>What is chemical peeling? Chemical peels are carried out by dermatologist as an in-clinic procedure to manage various skin concerns. The procedure involves application of specific chemical agents in pre-determined concentrations on to the skin. Get appointment Call us 96501 44438 F.A.Qs About Chemical peeling How is it done? At Garekars MD, the peeling session [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":3219,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":[],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/garekarsmdskinclinic.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/2686"}],"collection":[{"href":"http